definitions: a person or group that deprives others of power or prevents something from happening

examples.text: the biggest suppressor of democracy all over the world

shortDefinitions: person or group that restrains by depriving others of power

definitions: something that prevents the development or expression of a feeling, process, etc.

examples.text: that great suppressor of talent and imagination: fear
cannabis is a potent suppressor of the immune system

shortDefinitions: something that prevents development of feeling etc.

definitions: a device that partly or wholly eliminates electrical interference

examples.text: the computer and phone line are plugged into a surge suppressor

shortDefinitions: device that partly or wholly eliminates electrical interference
